cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for instance-level segmentation using RGB-D data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method is designed for autonomous robots, which suggests a potential application in robotics (cs.RO). The use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and object-centric training loss indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions the importance of safe and robust decision-making, which could be related to the field of robotics and control (cs.GR).
